         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>88f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>129</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>135</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... and for them at harvest time the tree did not ripen or yield / and for them the canes did not ripen at the [right] time</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Und nicht wurden ihnen die Baumfrüchte zur [rechten] Zeit reif [und] kamen nicht zustande.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">And the fruit of the trees did not ripen [for] them at the [right] time and did not come into being.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>129, 135</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3 #a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>161f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>14, 62</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Zahllos machte der Buddha Anstrengung, die[se] Wesen zur Entsagung zu bringen, in langer Zeit (in) [jedem] einzelnen (Augenblick). [Aber] sie entsagten eben (nicht).</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">The Buddha made attempts without number to bring the beings to renouncement, in a long time (in) [every] single (moment). [But] they did (not) renounce.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>161-2</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>34</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4 #a5 #a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>104</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>141</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1972"/><citedRange>461</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1993"/><citedRange>209</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Mit großer Mühe [und] Anstrengung zog ihn der Buddha aus dem Hause. [Da] er [sein] Denken an eine Frau gehängt [hatte], duldete er [es nämlich] nicht, zu entsagen.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">With great effort [and] exertion the Buddha pulled him out of the house. [Since] he [had] attached [his] thinking to a woman, he [could] not bear [it] to renounce [her].</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>470</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>14, 234</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(after)wards (he) l(e)d ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Alsdann führte er  [scil. der Buddha] (ihn zu den Göttern). [Aber erst] als er ihn von da in die Hölle führte, entsagte er.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Thereupon he [i.e. the Buddha] led (him to the gods). [But it was only] when he led him from thence into hell [that] he abjured.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>386</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>404 n.6</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>205</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1 #b2 #b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>104</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>719</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>34</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>214</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>500 n.5</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1969"/><citedRange>237</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the god Brahman himself kept him away ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4 #b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>105 and n.2</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>500 n.7</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
